The child should keep reading from user strings and send it to the parent to check if it is palindrome or not.
The parent should receive the request from the child. Once a request is received, it checks if it is palindrome or not, print the result, and send to the client the result. 
The child should print the results based on the received answer from the parent, and continue reading the next string.
